"Delivery ton badh jeh maa nu dudh kat aa reha hove tan maa nu changa paushtik khana davo jis vich hariyan sabzian, phal, dudh, dahi paneer teh je masahri tan ande, meat, machi bhi khao. zyada masale wala ya taliya hoya khana na khao.iodine wala namak khao. Din vich 8-10 glass paani pio, eh maa da dudh vadhan vich madad karda hai.
eh zaruri hai ki tussi bache nu dudh pilaunde raho es naal bache nu dudh chungan vich madad milugi. dhyan rakho ki bache nu maa de dudh to alawa kuch na davo.

delivery ton badh, 6 mahinyian tak tuhanu bache nu uparla kuch vi nai dena chahida, jivein ki pani, shehed, gan ya bari da dudh aadi es nal bache vich ultiyan ate tatiyan lag sakdiyan hun bache nu maa da dudh pilao har 2-3 gante, 20 minute layi, dono chatiyan ton eh bache de vadhan, ate theek rehan layi zaruri hai

Jeh tuhade bache ne bahut bar poty keeti hai ek din vich, tan dast de lachan dekho jivein ki - paani vargi poty, poty vich khoon aana , rang da badal jana.. jeh tussi eh dekho tan bache nu dudh pilande raho ate aspatal leke jao bina deri keete. Je poty aam dikhdi hai jivein roz aandi hai par bacha zyada bar kar reha hai phir vi bache nu aspatal leke jao. Jeh bache nu patli tatti aa rahi hai din vich ekk bar ton zyada tan bache nu aspatal leke jao Bache nu maa da dudh pilao hat 2 ghante vich tanki ohdi paani di kami na hove Jeh bache nu peshab kut aa reha hai ja gude rang da hai tan bache vich paani di kami hai delivery ton badh, 6 mahinyian tak tuhanu bache nu uparla kuch vi nai dena chahida, jivein ki pani, shehed, gan ya bari da dudh aadi es nal bache vich ultiyan ate tatiyan lag sakdiyan hun bache nu maa da dudh pilao har 2-3 gante, 20 minute layi, dono chatiyan ton eh bache de vadhan, ate theek rehan layi zaruri hai"

After delivery, for 6 months, you must not feed the baby anything else such as. water, honey, gripe water, cows milk, goats milk etc. this leads to vomitting and diarhoea in children. Breastfeed your baby every 2 - 3 hours.for 20 minutes each time, both breasts. this is all a baby needs for its growth, increase in weight , total well being "To burp your baby: 1. Hold the baby over your shoulder 2. Take care that the head of the baby is turned outward and the baby can breathe properly 3. Pat over the baby‚Äôs back gently or rub the back from upwards to downwards 4. Keep in this position till the baby is able to burp!" KMC_"Providing warmth to the baby by putting the baby without clothes, on the bare chest of the mother, father or any family member, is skin to skin care or kangaroo mother care. This is an easy and very effective method to take care of pre-term, low birth weight and normal newborn babies. get regular Immunization and regular follow-up ( Immunisation Chart for baby - at birth -OPV-0, Hep B, BCG 1 and half month - OPV-1, Rota-1, flPV-1, PCV-1 and Penta-1 2 and half month - OPV-2, Rota-2, Penta-2 3 and half month - OPV-3, Rota-3, flPV-2, PCV-2 and Penta-3 9 to 12 month - MR-1, JE-1, Vitamin A-1, PCV booster 16 to 24 month - DTP Booster-1, Vitamin A -2, MR-2, JE-2, OPV booster 5 to 6 years- DPT Booster-2, 10 year - TT 16 year - TT Get immunisation done as per schedule on the day advised by the doctor, take a look at the mother child card for more information on immunisation."

During pregancy it is advised that you do light exercises regularly and you may carry on witb small house hold chores. remember you must not lift weight or do any strenous exercise. walking for 20 -30 minutes a day , yoga etc are good and easy exercises. However, if you are advised by the doctor against exercising for medical reasons, kindly follow the advice.
yoga is extremely beneficial for you. But it is very very important that you do so under the guidance of a trained yoga teacher only
Yoga should involve stretching exercises which will help with back pains. If you have any history of preterm labour or have taken any treatment for the same in the current pregnancy, avoid exercises that involve squatting or pressure in lower abdomen.¬†
In the last months squatting is helpful to get the baby down and helps with labour

If everything is normal in the baby, a baby should be started on semisolid meals form 6 months. The diet shall include khichri 2 times a day, ghee can be added. Suji kheer once a day, daliya (finely ground wheat) once a day, halwa once a day, and mashed potatoes with rice (not potatoe alone) once a day. Veggies can be added to khichri or daliya either whole or steamed and ground. The main idea is to give whole grain and anaaj to the baby,
Breastfeed every 4-6 hours.
Feed the baby other food items for breakfast and lunch and a little in the evening. For dinner you can breastfeed the child.
Each child eats differently. A mother will be the best judge to know if her child is full.
Start small and slowly increase the dosage.
Remember to feed the child one thing only for a few days before introducing another item

It is preferable to sleep on the left side because it improves circulation and is generally more comfortable as you progress in pregnancy. sleeping on the right is ok however left is preferred.¬†
Use pillows to increase comfort.¬†
Get enough sleep at night and and at least 2 hours of rest in the day! Sleep on your side, facing your left"
